Hi, I do have the same problem actually. This seems to be a version mismatch between the generating Tensorflow version and the interpreting one. See [here](https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/issues/15698)

I recently built the tensorflow_core.a by myself with as stated [here](https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/tree/master/tensorflow/examples/ios#building-the-tensorflow-ios-libraries-from-source). But still can't get it run.
